UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. description.narrative: UNICEF supported Government and other stakeholder efforts towards the reduction of child marriage, whose prevalence has declined from 26.8% (2016) to 23.3%, as per NHFS-5 (2021) data. In 17 States, UNICEF reached nearly 11 million adolescents (70% being girls) with services and 13 million parents and community members to raise awareness on ECM and EVAC/GBV. UNICEF has leveraged more than 60 million (33% increase compared to 40 million in 2020) from government resources to prevent ECM. District action plans on ECM and adolescent empowerment operationalized in 175 districts (from 144 districts in 2020) in 10 states. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
